Using Locals to avoid code duplication
---------------------------------------
Locals/Local values : Named values that u can reference in other parts of your terraform code.
* Most often referred to as "locals", think of locals like short-term memory for your terraform code.
* They centralize and store values you use often, like names, env or shared tags.
* Local values can be helpful to avoid repeating the same values or expressions multiple times in a config.

locals {
  app_name = "app"
  environment = "dev"
}
call it with : local.app_name or local.environment
benefits  : central point to make changes, clearer code , less risk of unwanted changes.
